Class MachinePlayer

java.lang.Object
  java.util.Observable
      controller.Player
          controller.MachinePlayer
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Observer
public class MachinePlayer
extends Player

The MachinePlayer class is a mutable class that decides on a move depending on the given board configuration of an antichess game. This class uses a basic minimax technique of searching through the possible outcomes of a given set of moves to try and maximize its outcome.

  • timed : boolean //True iff the game is timed

makeMove

public java.lang.String makeMove(java.lang.String opponentMove,
                                 int timeLeft,
                                 int opponentTimeLeft)
Requires:
opponentMove be either a String representing a valid move by the opponent on the board stored in this (in the "standard string format" defined by the assignment), or the empty String. Also, timeLeft > 0 && opponentTimeLeft > 0.
Effects:
Returns a valid next move for this player in a String of the appropriate format, given the opponent's move, the time left for this player, and the time left for the opponent. (Both times are in milliseconds.) If opponentMove is the empty String, then the board for this player should be considered up to date (as would be the case if this player is asked to make the first move of the game). NOTE: This procedure may run greater than timeLeft, but this would mean losing the game.
Modifies:
this
